channel.title: Some Interesting Things I Found
channel.description:
I was recently going through boxes and I found some [b][i]interesting things.[/i][/b]
First I found a Red Rider BB Gun-it's the real thing too. I'm slightly afraid to use it for fear of having my eye shot out.
Next I found a German SA and Hitlers youth knife-I honestly have no idea why I have these, but I'm glad I do.
The last [b][i]mildly interesting[/i][/b] thing I found was an untitled book from the 1900's-it's a pretty good book from what I've read so far. It's about a guy living in Chicago during that time. It's pretty cool, it doesn't have any plot, it just sort of goes through events in his life. Very naturalistic.
Go through boxes and post what you find. They might be [i][b]interesting[/b][/i].

item.title: Some Interesting Things I Found
item.dc:creator: papernick
item.description:
Dr. Strangelove:

It’s not a diary, it’s just the writers style, and I think the cover might have been switched. It’s telling the story in first/person. I’m pretty sure the writer was trying to get the naturalistic style. I’ll show you what I mean with quotes and whatnot later, when I can get the book.

But until then, look around and post your interesting findings.

@Acristof: it wasn’t a joke.

transcribe a paragraph of it to google and see if anything comes up.
